d 'ADTEST': module to perform a two-sample Anderson-Darling equality-of-distributions test
d
d  adtest performs a (optionally weighted) two-sample
d Anderson-Darling (AD) permutation test to assess whether two
d samples come from the same distribution. The AD statistic
d standardizes the squared discrepancy between the two empirical
d cumulative distribution functions (ECDFs) by its variance under
d the null, which is smallest at the center of the pooled
d distribution and largest near its tails, making it most sensitive
d to a discrepancy concentrated in the tails, and better suited
d than Cramer-von Mises (cvmtest) to that case, though less
d sensitive than Kolmogorov-Smirnov (kstest) to a single large,
d localized discrepancy in the center of the distribution. The
d permutation test provides a valid p-value by comparing the
d observed statistic to its distribution under random reassignment
d of group labels. 
d
d KW: equality of distributions
d KW: two-sample
d KW: comparisons
d KW: weighting
d
d Requires: Stata version 11
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260717
d
d Author: Ariel Linden, Linden Consulting Group, LLC
d Support: email alinden@@lindenconsulting.org
d
f adtest.ado
f adtest.sthlp
